00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:08,233
ESPECIALLY AT CHRISTMAS.

246
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:11,900
THIS IS YOUR FATHER.

247
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,932
MY SON <i>LOVED</i> CHRISTMAS.

248
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:19,699
IT WAS HIS FAVORITE
TIME OF THE YEAR

249
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,899
SINCE HE WAS A LITTLE BOY.

250
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:24,199
MINE, TOO.

251
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,766
MAYBE A LITTLE MORE NOW.

252
00:14:25,767 --> 00:14:27,866
OH...

253
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,299
OH, WELL, LET'S, UH...

254
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:31,866
LET'S GET YOU TO YOUR ROOM.

255
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:33,100
JUST FOLLOW ME.

256
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,933
THIS FOOD LOOKS GOOD.

257
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,499
JOIN US, PLEASE.

258
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,766
OKAY.

259
00:14:42,767 --> 00:14:44,566
WAIT. NO, THAT'S DADDY'S!

260
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:45,567
OH.

261
00:14:45,568 --> 00:14:48,733
HOW ABOUT I SIT NEXT TO YOU?

262
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:52,200
WE WAITED FOR YOU.

263
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,399
THANKS.

264
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,866
OH NO, NO... TSS, TSS.

265
00:14:56,867 --> 00:14:58,799
OH, OKAY.

266
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,199
OKAY.

267
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:03,432
THANK YOU FOR THE FOOD
WE'RE ABOUT TO RECEIVE,

268
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:06,066
AND THANK YOU
FOR BRINGING OUR HALLE

269
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:09,066
TO JOIN US AT THIS TABLE.

270
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:10,067
AMEN.

271
00:15:10,068 --> 00:15:11,533
- AMEN.
- AMEN. - AMEN. - AMEN.

272
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:17,332
SO, HALLE, HIT US
WITH YOUR STORY.

273
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,532
MM-MM, NO.

274
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:21,532
WE'RE NOT GOING TO HAVE
AN INTERROGATION OVER LUNCH.

275
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:22,866
WE CAN'T GET SOME BASIC INFO?

276
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:24,566
MM-MM, MM-MM.

277
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,966
WHAT DO YOU DO?

278
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:31,132
I, UH... I WORK IN PUBLISHING.

279
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:32,399
DID YOU GROW UP IN CHICAGO?

280
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,532
YES, BORN AND RAISED.

281
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:36,232
YOU PLAY ANY SPORTS? NOT REALLY.

282
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:37,766
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

283
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:39,199
I WANT TO PLAY FOOTBALL.

284
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,499
GO, SAINTS!

285
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,432
NO, HE'S BASICALLY
A CHESS PRODIGY,

286
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:45,299
I PREFER HE FOCUS ON THAT.

287
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,566
OH. HE PLAYS ANYONE, ANYWHERE.

288
00:15:47,567 --> 00:15:49,233
SO, YOU'RE A GENIUS.

289
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,566
WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU TWO?

290
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,299
WELL, I'M A PUBLICIST IN L.A.

291
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:57,466
I ONLY WORK WITH
THE BIGGEST CELEBRITIES.

292
00:15:57,467 --> 00:16:00,066
I'M IN L.A., TOO.
I'M AN ENTREPRENEUR.

293
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:02,432
YEAH, WELL, NONE OF US
KNOW EXACTLY

294
00:16:02,433 --> 00:16:04,233
WHAT YOU'RE ENTREPRENEURING IN.

295
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,399
MAYBE STEPMOMMY-DEAREST
SHOULD GO NEXT.

296
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,232
SHE WORKED AT DADDY'S COMPANY.

297
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,066
WERE YOU A RECEPTIONIST?

298
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:14,932
OR A SECRETARY?

299
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:16,832
I WAS VICE PRESIDENT
OF MARKETING.

300
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,166
I HIRED THE PUBLICIST

301
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:21,232
THAT, UH, PRINCESS SPOILED HERE
IS TRYING TO BECOME.

302
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:24,266
NOW, THAT'S ENOUGH OF THAT.

303
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:27,099
SO, DO YOU ALL HAVE
MANY CHRISTMAS TRADITIONS?

304
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,732
DOESN'T EVERYBODY?

305
00:16:28,733 --> 00:16:30,532
YES, WE DO, AND WE WANT YOU

306
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:33,399
TO EXPERIENCE
ALL OF THEM WITH US.

307
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,266
THERE ARE PARTIES.

308
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:39,266
ONE HERE, AND THE
ANNUAL FETE QUARTIER.

309
00:16:39,267 --> 00:16:40,599
IT'S WONDERFUL.

310
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,432
MUSIC, DANCING.

311
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:44,332
SO MUCH FOOD AND EVERYTHING.

312
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:48,566
TOO MUCH, HONESTLY.

313
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:50,266
UH, DO YOU USUALLY
SPEND CHRISTMAS

314
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:52,466
WITH YOUR ADOPTIVE FAMILY?

315
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,499
NO, I WAS ADOPTED AS A BABY,

316
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:56,366
BUT I GREW UP IN FOSTER CARE.

317
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:59,366
WE HAVEN'T GOTTEN THAT FAR YET.

318
00:16:59,367 --> 00:17:01,566
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY PARENTS?

319
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:03,232
I'VE HAD LOTS OF THEM,

320
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:06,432
AND A REALLY GREAT
SOCIAL WORKER NAMED EUGENE.

321
00:17:06,433 --> 00:17:08,066
WE'RE STILL CLOSE.

322
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:09,067
HMM.

323
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,632
THIS FOOD IS REALLY GOOD.

324
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:20,532
YEAH.

325
00:17:20,533 --> 00:17:21,633
MM-HMM. ALWAYS.

326
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,199
OH, GOD.

327
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,366
I CAN HEAT SOMETHING UP
FOR YOU, IF YOU LIKE.

328
00:18:02,367 --> 00:18:04,799
JUST LOOKING FOR
SOMETHING SWEET.

329
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,599
OKAY.

330
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,432
WHAT DO YOU HAVE A TASTE FOR?

331
00:18:08,433 --> 00:18:12,599
SOMETHING WITH SUGAR IN IT,
ON IT, AND WITH IT.

332
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:15,066
WITH IT, OKAY.

333
00:18:15,067 --> 00:18:17,499
TELL YOU WHAT... I GOT AN IDEA.

334
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,766
COME WITH ME. OKAY.

335
00:18:19,767 --> 00:18:23,566
SO, WHAT'S CHRISTMAS LIKE
IN CHICAGO?

336
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:24,932
COLD.

337
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:27,099
SNOW IS ALREADY ON THE GROUND.

338
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,832
SOME NIGHTS, IT'S
WHAT YOU WOULD IMAGINE

339
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:31,766
A WINTER WONDERLAND IS.

340
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:34,433
IS THAT SNOWMEN
IN BIG PUFFY COATS?

341
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:39,699
I DON'T KNOW ANY OTHER
KIND OF CHRISTMAS.

342
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,599
I'VE SPENT ALL OF THEM THERE.

343
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:45,632
THAT'S WHY I WANT TO KNOW
EVERYTHING ABOUT CHRISTMAS HERE.

344
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:46,766
WELL, I CAN TELL YOU,
FOR THE MOORES,

345
00:18:46,767 --> 00:18:49,199
THERE'S PLENTY OF
TRADITIONS AND EVENTS

346
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,699
EVERY DAY OF THE WEEK
FOR CHRISTMAS.

347
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:51,932
HMM. NOW, AS FOR ME,

348
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:53,399
I'M COOKING FOR THEIR
ANNUAL REVEILLON DINNER

349
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,832
FOR THE COMPANY EXECUTIVES.

350
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:57,432
WHAT'S A "REVEILLON DINNER"?

351
00:18:57,433 --> 00:19:00,199
IT'S A FESTIVE DINNER MEANT
TO AWAKEN THE CHRISTMAS SPIRIT.

352
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:03,732
IT'S A VERY OLD TRADITION
HERE IN NEW ORLEANS.

353
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:05,632
AND YOU GO TO ALL THESE EVENTS?

354
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:08,966
WELL, I GO TO THE ONES I WANT TO

355
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:10,799
AND COOK FOR THE ONES THEY HOST.

356
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,632
BUT CHRISTMAS DAY? MM-HMM?

357
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:14,532
ALWAYS WITH THE FAMILY.

358
00:19:14,533 --> 00:19:15,699
OH.

359
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:17,100
WIFE AND KIDS?

360
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,633
PARENTS AND SIBLINGS.

361
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:25,066
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

362
00:19:25,067 --> 00:19:27,566
YOU EVER GET A CHANCE
TO SPEND THOSE...

363
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:30,432
WINTER WONDERLAND MOMENTS
WITH ANYONE SPECIAL?

364
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:33,332
ONLY MY FORMER
SOCIAL WORKER, EUGENE.

365
00:19:33,333 --> 00:19:35,632
SO, LET ME ASK YOU THIS...

366
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:38,100
HOW ARE YOU HANDLING FINDING
OUT ABOUT YOUR NEW FAMILY?

367
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:44,366
NOT KNOWING WAS MUCH EASIER.

368
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:46,200
EASIER, YEAH. BUT BETTER?

369
00:19:48,067 --> 00:19:50,166
I'M NOT SURE YET.

370
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:52,299
DID YOU GUYS HAVE FUN?

371
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:54,499
HE INTRODUCED ME TO BEIGNETS.

372
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:56,599
OOH.

373
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,966
HE'S SUCH A FINE YOUNG MAN.

374
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:01,300
ALWAYS HAS BEEN.

375
00:20:05,567 --> 00:20:06,966
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

376
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:07,967
OH...

377
00:20:09,233 --> 00:20:12,700
YOU LOOK SO MUCH
LIKE YOUR FATHER.

378
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:19,466
I'M SORRY.

379
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:21,932
OH, BABY, NO.

380
00:20:21,933 --> 00:20:24,399
YOU LOOK LIKE MY SON.

381
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:28,333
PLEASE DON'T EVER
FEEL SORRY ABOUT THAT.

382
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:32,767
WHEN YOU'RE READY...

383
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,867
CALL ME "MEMAW."

384
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:39,733
GOOD NIGHT, BABY.

385
00:20:39,734 --> 00:20:40,867
GOOD NIGHT.

386
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,299
EVERY YEAR, THE CHAMPION HERE

387
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,466
REPRESENTS THEIR SCHOOL
AT THE CITY-WIDE CHESS SLAM

388
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:48,799
THAT'S IN A FEW DAYS.

389
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,099
OH, OKAY.

390
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:52,099
IS HE THAT GOOD? OH, HE IS.

391
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:53,532
HE HAS A COACH AND EVERYTHING.

392
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:55,366
I JUST WANT HIM
TO HAVE THE BEST LIFE.

393
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:56,367
MM-HMM.

394
00:20:56,368 --> 00:20:59,900
NOW, WITH HIS FATHER GONE...

395
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:04,066
IS ANY THE FAMILY HELPING YOU?

396
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:05,732
OH, I THANK GOD FOR MEMAW.

397
00:21:05,733 --> 00:21:07,966
I MEAN, SHE'S A LIFESAVER.

398
00:21:07,967 --> 00:21:10,799
BUT TIFFANY, SHE'S WRAPPED UP
IN HER OWN DADDY ISSUES,

399
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,567
AND GLENN JUST FOLLOWS HER LEAD.

400
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:18,166
HAVE YOU ASKED THEM
FOR THEIR HELP?

401
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:20,132
HAVE THEY OFFERED?

402
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:22,900
GOT IT.

403
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:26,066
WELL, WHAT ABOUT HOWARD?

404
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:27,767
WOULD YOU TELL ME ABOUT HIM?

405
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:31,699
HE WAS HILARIOUS.

406
00:21:31,700 --> 00:21:34,633
OH, WE LAUGHED SO MUCH
OVER THE YEARS.

407
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,132
HE WAS JUST SO KIND.

408
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:40,400
HE REALLY CARED ABOUT PEOPLE.

409
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:45,632
DID HOWARD TELL YOU ABOUT ME,

410
00:21:45,633 --> 00:21:49,599
OR DID YOU FIND OUT
WITH EVERYONE ELSE?

411
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:53,066
HE DID... A FEW YEARS
AFTER WE GOT MARRIED.

412
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:55,432
YOU KNOW, AFTER WE
HAD DREW, HE...

413
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:57,666
IT FELT LIKE
HE WAS HOLDING BACK.

414
00:21:57,667 --> 00:22:01,133
UNTIL I FINALLY ASKED HIM
ABOUT IT, AND TOLD ME.

415
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,532
HONESTLY, I DON'T...

416
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:07,100
THINK HE EVER GOT OVER
YOUR MOTHER AND WHAT HAPPENED.

417
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:11,832
WHY DO YOU THINK HE DIDN'T TELL

418
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:13,567
TIFFANY AND GLENN ABOUT ME?

419
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,466
I THINK HE WANTED TO,

420
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:21,533
BUT HE WAS WAITING
FOR THIS PERFECT MOMENT.

421
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:28,066
THERE REALLY IS NO PERFECT
MOMENT FOR THIS, IS THERE?

422
00:22:28,067 --> 00:22:29,367
MM-MM.

423
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:35,232
AND I WOULD APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU WOULDN'T SAY ANYTHING

424
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:37,933
TO TIFFANY AND GLENN
ABOUT ME KNOWING.

425
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:41,666
EVEN THOUGH
THEY KEEP THEIR DISTANCE,

426
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:44,333
I'LL ALWAYS BE
PROTECTIVE OF THEM.

427
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:47,967
THAT MUST BE REALLY HARD ON YOU.

428
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:52,400
SO, WHAT'S NEXT FOR YOU?

429
00:22:54,467 --> 00:22:59,066
UH, I'M WORKING ON A BOOK
FOR FEMALE EXECUTIVES

430
00:22:59,067 --> 00:23:03,166
ABOUT WHAT TO DO
TO PLAN PROPERLY...

431
00:23:03,167 --> 00:23:05,066
YOU KNOW, FOR CAREER AND FAMILY.

432
00:23:05,067 --> 00:23:08,732
SO, YOU WANTED TO
GO BACK TO WORK?

433
00:23:08,733 --> 00:23:10,666
MY ORIGINAL PLAN WAS MONTHS,

434
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:12,633
AND IT TURNED INTO YEARS.

435
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:17,299
SO, PLAN FOR WHEN
THE PLANS CHANGE.

436
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:18,733
BASICALLY. MM.

437
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:23,466
WANT ME TO TAKE A LOOK AT
WHAT YOU'VE WRITTEN SO FAR?

438
00:23:23,467 --> 00:23:25,632
OH, THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU WORK FOR A PUBLISHER.

439
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:27,133
YEAH. DOING WHAT, EXACTLY?

440
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:31,532
OH, UM, PROOFREADING.

441
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,733
I... I PROOF MANUSCRIPTS.

442
00:23:34,733 --> 00:23:38,166
OH, WELL, IT SEEMS LIKE
YOU'D KNOW WHAT YOU DO.

443
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:42,699
WELL, WHEN I'M READY TO PROOF,
I KNOW WHO TO CALL.

444
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,666
AND WHEN YOU'RE READY
TO BE HONEST WITH ME

445
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:47,767
ABOUT WHAT YOU DO,
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.

446
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,832
HEY, BIG MAMA. WHAT UP, BIG SIS?

447
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:54,066
WHY DOES EVERY NICKNAME
FOR THE WOMEN IN YOUR LIFE

448
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:56,966
INCLUDE THE WORD "BIG" IN IT?

449
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:59,066
I MEAN...

450
00:23:59,067 --> 00:24:00,666
YOU KNOW...

451
00:24:00,667 --> 00:24:03,066
Y'ALL SHOULD SHOW HALLE HERE
SOME GOOD SOUTHERN HOSPITALITY

452
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:05,332
AND SHOW HER AROUND TOWN.

453
00:24:05,333 --> 00:24:07,799
WE WOULD, BUT GLENN AND I WERE

454
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,432
JUST HEADED OUT SOMEWHERE.

455
00:24:09,433 --> 00:24:11,066
MM-HMM.

456
00:24:11,067 --> 00:24:12,232
IT'S FINE.

457
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:14,366
I'M TIRED, AND I'VE GOT TO
GET SOME WORK DONE.

458
00:24:14,367 --> 00:24:16,399
OH, NO, NO. TAKE HALLE.

459
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:19,066
I MEAN, YOU GUYS SHOULD START
DOING THINGS TOGETHER...

460
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:23,666
YOU KNOW, SINCE THE DUO
IS NOW A TRIO, AND ALL.

461
00:24:23,667 --> 00:24:25,732
FINE.

462
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:28,233
BUT YOU TWO ARE GONNA NEED
TO PUT ON SOME NICER CLOTHES.

463
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,899
SHE BROUGHT THAT CAR
TO SHOW MEMAW

464
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,466
HER FIRST GROWN-UP PURCHASE.

465
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:37,967
SHE KEEPS IT SPOTLESS.

466
00:24:41,867 --> 00:24:44,132
THIS FOOD BETTER MAKE ME
FORGIVE HOW FAST YOU DROVE

467
00:24:44,133 --> 00:24:46,132
THROUGH EVERYTHING
I'LL HAVE TO SEE AGAIN.

468
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:48,099
AH-AH-AH, YOU MIGHT
BE FROM CHI-TOWN,

469
00:24:48,100 --> 00:24:50,799
BUT DON'T UNDERESTIMATE
NEW ORLEANS CUISINE, BIG SIS.

470
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:54,066
GLENN, DON'T MAKE ME AGREE
WITH YOUR STEPMOTHER.

471
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:55,566
ENOUGH WITH THE "BIGS."

472
00:24:55,567 --> 00:24:56,700
LEAVE IT IN FRONT.

473
00:25:04,867 --> 00:25:07,332
SO, YOU HUNG OUT
WITH JOAN THIS MORNING.

474
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:09,332
HOW WAS THAT?

475
00:25:09,333 --> 00:25:10,533
NOT BAD.

476
00:25:11,967 --> 00:25:14,066
WE TALKED.

477
00:25:14,067 --> 00:25:16,066
JOAN'S HOT AND COLD.

478
00:25:16,067 --> 00:25:17,599
SHE STARTS OFF HOT,

479
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,399
BUT AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,

480
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,899
SHE'S JUST COLD TO US.

481
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:23,066
HOW DID SHE GO FROM HOT TO COLD?

482
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:25,066
WHEN HER AND DADDY GOT MARRIED,

483
00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:26,232
SHE TRIED WITH US.

484
00:25:26,233 --> 00:25:28,066
IT WAS LIKE WE WERE A FAMILY.

485
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:29,766
BUT THEN SHE HAD DREW,

486
00:25:29,767 --> 00:25:33,366
AND WE WENT FROM BEING HER KIDS
TO BEING HER STEPKIDS.

