728
00:36:42,434 --> 00:36:44,433
I'LL SHOW YOU HOW BAD I AM.

729
00:36:47,367 --> 00:36:52,067
IS IT OKAY IF I ASKED YOU
WHAT FOSTER CARE WAS LIKE?

730
00:36:52,967 --> 00:36:54,399
HMMM.

731
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:57,866
WELL, THERE'S A BOOK SERIES

732
00:36:57,867 --> 00:36:59,832
CALLED "CHRISTINA KICK-BUTT"...

733
00:36:59,833 --> 00:37:02,099
I KNOW ABOUT CHRISTINA.

734
00:37:02,100 --> 00:37:05,499
WELL, CHRISTINA TALKS
ABOUT ALL THE SKILLS

735
00:37:05,500 --> 00:37:07,966
SHE LEARNS AT HER GROUP HOMES.

736
00:37:07,967 --> 00:37:09,567
THAT'S WHAT IT WAS LIKE FOR ME.

737
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:22,332
CHESS ISN'T A GAME
ABOUT ANY ONE PIECE.

738
00:37:22,333 --> 00:37:26,532
EACH MOVE IS ABOUT
ALL OF THE PIECES.

739
00:37:26,533 --> 00:37:28,566
THEY'RE CONNECTED.

740
00:37:28,567 --> 00:37:33,299
SO, WHEN YOU MOVE
THE WHOLE BOARD AT ONCE,

741
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:36,599
YOU'RE NOT JUST A PAWN ANYMORE.

742
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:38,332
BE THE BOARD,

743
00:37:38,333 --> 00:37:40,400
A-AND NOT JUST A PIECE.

744
00:37:42,533 --> 00:37:43,533
HEY.

745
00:37:43,534 --> 00:37:44,899
I'LL BE TAKING YOU TO PRACTICE.

746
00:37:44,900 --> 00:37:47,067
GO AHEAD. I'LL KEEP STUDYING.

747
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:49,866
I'LL BE CHECKING OUT THE VENUE

748
00:37:49,867 --> 00:37:52,566
ONCE I DROP OFF MY BABY BROTHER.

749
00:37:52,567 --> 00:37:54,900
OKAY, BYE.

750
00:37:56,933 --> 00:37:59,166
YOU'RE TAKING HIM TO PRACTICE?

751
00:37:59,167 --> 00:38:00,399
YEAH.

752
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:01,732
YOU WERE RIGHT.

753
00:38:01,733 --> 00:38:04,667
WHEN I GOT BACK, I ASKED JOAN,
AND SHE SAID, "OKAY."

754
00:38:07,167 --> 00:38:09,700
HE'S GONNA BREAK HIS NECK.

755
00:38:12,767 --> 00:38:13,799
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

756
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:15,499
YOU'RE GONNA FALL. NO, HE WON'T.

757
00:38:15,500 --> 00:38:17,066
I'LL HELP HIM.

758
00:38:17,067 --> 00:38:18,166
SEE?

759
00:38:18,167 --> 00:38:19,733
SHE'S NOT SO BAD.

760
00:38:21,333 --> 00:38:22,666
PRACTICALLY HAVE TO FLY

761
00:38:22,667 --> 00:38:24,233
TO GET DREW TO PRACTICE ON TIME.

762
00:38:25,867 --> 00:38:28,367
NOT LIKE SHE WAS GONNA SPEED
THE WHOLE WAY ANYWAY, RIGHT?

763
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,133
LET ME SHOW YOU WHAT I DID.

764
00:38:36,433 --> 00:38:37,732
DON'T YOU FORGET
NOTHING, ALL RIGHT?

765
00:38:37,733 --> 00:38:39,066
I'M NOT.

766
00:38:39,067 --> 00:38:41,399
YOU DON'T FORGET
THIS INGREDIENT.

767
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,766
YES.

768
00:38:42,767 --> 00:38:45,232
WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE?

769
00:38:45,233 --> 00:38:46,832
I HAVE A GINGERBREAD RECIPE,

770
00:38:46,833 --> 00:38:49,800
AND DEVIN IS PICKING UP
SOME INGREDIENTS FOR ME.

771
00:38:51,067 --> 00:38:53,932
OH, YOU COOK DESSERTS, TOO.

772
00:38:53,933 --> 00:38:55,833
HALLE, WHAT DON'T YOU DO?

773
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:01,066
JOAN, I'M SORRY ABOUT YESTERDAY.

774
00:39:01,067 --> 00:39:01,967
I SCREWED UP.

775
00:39:01,968 --> 00:39:04,199
AND ABOUT DREW. IT'S FINE.

776
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:05,832
THE TWINS NEEDED TO
KNOW THE TRUTH,

777
00:39:05,833 --> 00:39:08,533
AND DREW RAVED ABOUT
HOW MUCH FUN YOU ALL HAD.

778
00:39:10,433 --> 00:39:12,166
SO, WE'RE OKAY?

779
00:39:12,167 --> 00:39:13,566
OF COURSE.

780
00:39:13,567 --> 00:39:16,432
I WAS THE NEW MEMBER
OF THIS FAMILY ONCE.

781
00:39:16,433 --> 00:39:19,099
THE MOORES MAKE YOU
EARN YOUR SPOT,

782
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:20,400
ESPECIALLY TIFFANY.

783
00:39:21,567 --> 00:39:24,299
IT'LL TAKE YEARS...
LIKE IT DID FOR ME...

784
00:39:24,300 --> 00:39:25,799
BUT YOU'LL SETTLE INTO

785
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,933
A COMFORTABLE GROOVE EVENTUALLY.

786
00:39:29,733 --> 00:39:31,499
BUT YOU'LL GET THERE FASTER

787
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:33,733
IF YOU'RE NOT KEEPING US
AT A DISTANCE.

788
00:39:37,967 --> 00:39:39,199
THAT SUIT IS FIRE.

789
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:40,932
OH, YOU LIKE IT? MM-HMM.

790
00:39:40,933 --> 00:39:42,199
I'M GOING TO A HOLIDAY LUNCHEON

791
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:44,466
WITH THE WIVES OF THE
EXECUTIVES AT THE COMPANY.

792
00:39:44,467 --> 00:39:46,399
THEY NEED TO KNOW
I STILL GOT IT.

793
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:48,567
OKAY.

794
00:40:00,767 --> 00:40:02,699
I WAS WONDERING WHEN
YOU WOULD FINALLY CHECK IN.

795
00:40:02,700 --> 00:40:04,032
I'M SORRY.

796
00:40:04,033 --> 00:40:06,066
IT'S BEEN A WHIRLWIND
SINCE I GOT HERE.

797
00:40:06,067 --> 00:40:07,299
IT'S GOOD.

798
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:09,832
WELL, FIRST OF ALL,
THIS PHONE IS A GAME-CHANGER.

799
00:40:09,833 --> 00:40:11,666
OH, I WOULD HAVE GOT YOU ONE
A LONG TIME AGO

800
00:40:11,667 --> 00:40:13,432
IF I'D KNOWN ALL THAT.

801
00:40:13,433 --> 00:40:14,966
<i>HEY, MY BROTHER AND HIS FAMILY</i>

802
00:40:14,967 --> 00:40:16,532
<i>ARE COMING OVER FOR CHRISTMAS.</i>

803
00:40:16,533 --> 00:40:18,166
<i>I DON'T KNOW HOW TO THANK YOU.</i>

804
00:40:18,167 --> 00:40:21,866
GENE, HEARING ALL THIS
GOOD NEWS IS THANK YOU ENOUGH.

805
00:40:21,867 --> 00:40:23,699
OH, ENOUGH ABOUT ME.

806
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:25,932
TELL ME ABOUT NEW ORLEANS.

807
00:40:25,933 --> 00:40:28,199
ARE YOU GETTING THE ANSWERS
TO HELP UNBLOCK YOU?

808
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:31,132
NOT YET.

809
00:40:31,133 --> 00:40:32,699
I'M REALLY SCARED.

810
00:40:32,700 --> 00:40:35,299
I ONLY HAVE A FEW MORE DAYS
TO GET THIS IN.

811
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:36,300
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M GONNA DO

812
00:40:36,301 --> 00:40:37,999
IF I CAN'T WRITE
CHRISTINA ANYMORE.

813
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,166
<i>NEVER GON' HAPPEN.</i>

814
00:40:39,167 --> 00:40:40,833
<i>TELL ME SOMETHING HAPPIER.</i>

815
00:40:42,100 --> 00:40:44,000
HOLD ON, GENE. COME IN!

816
00:40:47,067 --> 00:40:49,266
MEMAW WANTED ME TO
MAKE SURE YOU WERE SET

817
00:40:49,267 --> 00:40:51,666
FOR TONIGHT'S REVEILLON DINNER.

818
00:40:51,667 --> 00:40:53,266
I'LL TRY YOU LATER.
<i>ALL RIGHT, BYE.</i>

819
00:40:53,267 --> 00:40:55,366
OKAY, BYE. I'M SET.

820
00:40:55,367 --> 00:40:57,266
UH, MY DRESS IS IN THE CLOSET.

821
00:40:57,267 --> 00:40:59,332
OH, MAY I?

822
00:40:59,333 --> 00:41:00,467
GO AHEAD.

823
00:41:03,633 --> 00:41:05,367
OH, THIS DRESS!

824
00:41:07,333 --> 00:41:09,199
WOW, HALLE.

825
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:11,100
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU CAME TO SLAY.

826
00:41:13,267 --> 00:41:15,599
BUT, YOU KNOW,
TONIGHT'S PARTY IS

827
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:17,699
AN UGLY CHRISTMAS SWEATER PARTY.

828
00:41:17,700 --> 00:41:19,966
OH, I THOUGHT IT WAS COCKTAIL.

829
00:41:19,967 --> 00:41:21,699
YEAH, WITH EVERYTHING
GOING ON THIS YEAR,

830
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:24,332
WE FIGURE, "LIGHTEN THE MOOD."

831
00:41:24,333 --> 00:41:25,932
LET'S GO SHOPPING
AND GET YOU ONE.

832
00:41:25,933 --> 00:41:27,299
OKAY.

833
00:41:27,300 --> 00:41:28,532
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

834
00:41:28,533 --> 00:41:30,600
OH, RIGHT NOW. OKAY, OKAY.

835
00:41:57,567 --> 00:41:59,667
I CAN EAT A LITTLE MORE
OF THESE.

836
00:42:02,733 --> 00:42:05,399
HALLE. COME, COME.

837
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:11,667
I'D LIKE TO INTRODUCE YOU TO
MY OTHER GRANDDAUGHTER, HALLE.

838
00:42:14,733 --> 00:42:16,066
EXCUSE ME.

839
00:42:16,067 --> 00:42:21,799
THIS IS CONSIDERED "DRESSED UP"
IN CHICAGO.

840
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:27,233
WISH I COULD TRADE YOU.

841
00:42:31,567 --> 00:42:33,600
YOU'RE REALLY
LIGHTING UP THE PLACE.

842
00:42:55,467 --> 00:42:58,232
"HOW DO YOU ACCEPT
THAT THE FAMILY"

843
00:42:58,233 --> 00:43:05,666
YOU HAVE DREAMED OF FOR
A LIFETIME IS A NIGHTMARE?

844
00:43:05,667 --> 00:43:09,600
"THIS ENTIRE MOORE
FAMILY IS FAKE."

845
00:43:18,900 --> 00:43:22,733
HEY. THIS IS FROM DEVIN.

846
00:43:26,633 --> 00:43:31,532
SO, WILL YOU TELL ME MORE
ABOUT THAT BOOK YOU MENTIONED?

847
00:43:31,533 --> 00:43:33,167
I CAN DO BETTER THAN THAT.

848
00:43:36,767 --> 00:43:38,866
THANK YOU! I'LL GO READ IT NOW.

849
00:43:38,867 --> 00:43:42,866
NO, THANK YOU. YOU ARE SO SWEET.

850
00:43:42,867 --> 00:43:45,799
YOU MAKE THIS MUCH EASIER.

851
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,633
WELL, I TAKE BEING
A BROTHER SERIOUSLY.

852
00:44:01,067 --> 00:44:03,432
YOU OWNED THAT SWEATER.

853
00:44:03,433 --> 00:44:04,899
I HAD TO.

854
00:44:04,900 --> 00:44:06,866
COULDN'T LET MY OPPONENTS
SEE ME BREAK DOWN.

855
00:44:06,867 --> 00:44:08,166
YEAH.

856
00:44:08,167 --> 00:44:11,532
SEEMS LIKE THIS FAMILY
BRINGS OUT THAT SIDE OF ME.

857
00:44:11,533 --> 00:44:13,132
DEFIANCE?

858
00:44:13,133 --> 00:44:14,567
RESILIENCE.

859
00:44:16,300 --> 00:44:18,966
ALRIGHT. LET'S GET TO COOKING.

860
00:44:18,967 --> 00:44:21,367
HERE WE GO. WE GOT
SOME APPLESAUCE.

861
00:44:24,567 --> 00:44:26,833
MM.

862
00:44:30,067 --> 00:44:33,666
THIS SMELLS AMAZING.

863
00:44:33,667 --> 00:44:35,566
GIVE EUGENE ALL THE CREDIT.

864
00:44:35,567 --> 00:44:38,266
I BURNED WATER BEFORE HE
AND HIS WIFE TAUGHT ME.

865
00:44:38,267 --> 00:44:40,832
OH, SORRY. WE SMELLED
SOMETHING GOOD.

866
00:44:40,833 --> 00:44:42,299
AH-AH!

867
00:44:42,300 --> 00:44:45,699
YOU'VE EARNED WHATEVER'S
ABOUT TO HAPPEN TO YOU.

868
00:44:45,700 --> 00:44:49,199
WANT SOME?

869
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:52,099
YOU'RE LUCKY I'M NOT GOING
SOUTH SIDE ON YOU TONIGHT.

870
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,566
LOOK, I DIDN'T MEAN TO...

871
00:44:54,567 --> 00:44:57,432
TO EMBARRASS ME IN
A ROOM FULL OF PEOPLE?

872
00:44:57,433 --> 00:45:00,099
OR TO TAINT WHAT I THOUGHT
WAS FINALLY A NICE DAY

873
00:45:00,100 --> 00:45:01,767
SPENT WITH MY NEW SISTER?

874
00:45:06,467 --> 00:45:07,732
D, THIS SMELLS AMAZING, MAN.

875
00:45:07,733 --> 00:45:11,532
OH, THIS ISN'T ME.
IT'S ALL HALLE.

876
00:45:11,533 --> 00:45:12,966
IT'S EUGENE'S RECIPE.

877
00:45:12,967 --> 00:45:14,299
HALLE.

878
00:45:14,300 --> 00:45:18,066
YOU COULD HAVE TOLD US YOU
NEEDED APPROPRIATE ATTIRE.

879
00:45:18,067 --> 00:45:20,366
YOU'VE BEEN SO TASTEFUL
IN YOUR CLOTHES UNTIL NOW.

880
00:45:20,367 --> 00:45:21,732
TALK TO TIFFANY.

881
00:45:21,733 --> 00:45:23,066
WHY WOULD I WEAR THAT SWEATER

882
00:45:23,067 --> 00:45:25,766
WHEN I HAVE A DESIGNER
COCKTAIL DRESS IN THE CLOSET?

883
00:45:25,767 --> 00:45:28,232
FINE, BUT I DON'T WANT
TO KEEP WORRYING ABOUT

884
00:45:28,233 --> 00:45:31,132
THE NEXT UNEXPECTED THING
YOU'RE GONNA DO OR SAY.

885
00:45:31,133 --> 00:45:34,566
IF YOU WANT ME TO TRUST YOU,
STOP COMING FOR ME LIKE THIS.

886
00:45:34,567 --> 00:45:36,633
TRUST IS A TWO-WAY STREET.

887
00:45:44,900 --> 00:45:45,933
MM!

888
00:45:50,800 --> 00:45:54,700
WHO'S GOING TO START?

889
00:45:58,500 --> 00:46:02,099
HEY.

890
00:46:02,100 --> 00:46:06,066
NO ONE HAS EVER DARED
TO DO THAT BEFORE.

891
00:46:06,067 --> 00:46:08,066
DONE WHAT?

892
00:46:08,067 --> 00:46:10,067
SAY EXACTLY WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

893
00:46:12,733 --> 00:46:16,700
AT THIS RATE, I DON'T KNOW THAT
I'LL MAKE IT TO CHRISTMAS DAY.

894
00:46:19,300 --> 00:46:21,366
YOU WILL.

895
00:46:21,367 --> 00:46:23,966
TRUST ME.

896
00:46:23,967 --> 00:46:29,666
MEMAW AND DREW, THEY'RE WORTH
PUTTING UP WITH THE CRAZY,

897
00:46:29,667 --> 00:46:31,566
SO STAY FOR THEM.

898
00:46:31,567 --> 00:46:33,199
HMM.

899
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,333
STAY FOR ME.

900
00:46:37,833 --> 00:46:39,732
WE ARE GOING TO GET THROUGH

901
00:46:39,733 --> 00:46:45,867
THIS FIRST CHRISTMAS
WITHOUT MY SON AS A FAMILY.

902
00:46:47,133 --> 00:46:48,632
AM I CLEAR?

903
00:46:48,633 --> 00:46:53,332
YES, MA'AM.

904
00:46:53,333 --> 00:46:56,799
HALLE, COME WITH ME.

905
00:46:56,800 --> 00:47:01,066
SHE ACTUALLY TOOK YOU SHOPPING
TO BUY THAT AWFUL SWEATER?

906
00:47:01,067 --> 00:47:02,499
SHE DID.

907
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:05,599
I'VE NEVER SEEN SOMEONE COMMIT
THAT HARD TO A PRANK.

908
00:47:05,600 --> 00:47:08,067
SHE'S A PUBLICIST FOR A REASON.

909
00:47:12,533 --> 00:47:14,432
JOAN'S RIGHT, THOUGH.

910
00:47:14,433 --> 00:47:16,967
I AM KEEPING
SOMETHING FROM YOU...

911
00:47:19,467 --> 00:47:23,499
BUT I'M ALSO KEEPING IT
FROM THE WHOLE WORLD.

912
00:47:23,500 --> 00:47:29,333
I DON'T WORK FOR A PUBLISHER.
THEY KIND OF WORK FOR ME.

913
00:47:31,933 --> 00:47:36,732
I WRITE UNDER
THE NAME H.D. MADISON.

914
00:47:36,733 --> 00:47:39,299
YOU WRITE THE "CHRISTINA" BOOKS.

915
00:47:39,300 --> 00:47:40,799
YOU KNOW ABOUT THEM?

916
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:43,499
I SIT ON THE BOARD OF A LIBRARY.

917
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:45,066
OF COURSE I KNOW ABOUT THEM.

918
00:47:45,067 --> 00:47:49,067
THE SUPERHERO OF... FOSTER CARE.

919
00:47:51,067 --> 00:47:53,299
OH, HALLE.

920
00:47:53,300 --> 00:47:58,166
YOU SHARE YOUR PAIN
AND YOUR TRIUMPHS.

921
00:47:58,167 --> 00:48:03,732
WHY NOT TELL THE WORLD
YOU'RE A WRITER?

922
00:48:03,733 --> 00:48:08,266
WELL, THERE'S A SHAME
TO FEELING UNWANTED.

923
00:48:08,267 --> 00:48:13,966
IT'S A SECRET THAT WALKS
INTO EVERY ROOM WITH ME.

924
00:48:13,967 --> 00:48:15,700
ANONYMITY IS FREEDOM.

925
00:48:17,867 --> 00:48:21,532
THANK YOU FOR
TRUSTING ME WITH THIS.

926
00:48:21,533 --> 00:48:24,466
I WON'T SAY A WORD.

927
00:48:24,467 --> 00:48:28,332
OH, HALLE... WOULD
YOU STOP A MINUTE?

928
00:48:28,333 --> 00:48:30,099
IT'S LATE. I'M HEADING TO BED.

929
00:48:30,100 --> 00:48:32,566
I EXPLODED EARLIER.

930
00:48:32,567 --> 00:48:34,632
I DIDN'T WANT HOWARD'S
BUSINESS ASSOCIATES

931
00:48:34,633 --> 00:48:37,299
BEING INTRODUCED
TO YOU THAT WAY.

932
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:38,600
NEITHER DID I.

933
00:48:40,867 --> 00:48:42,866
WAIT, IS THIS...?

934
00:48:42,867 --> 00:48:44,966
HOWARD'S OFFICE?

935
00:48:44,967 --> 00:48:47,499
IT IS.

936
00:48:47,500 --> 00:48:50,066
OH, HE WAS A HARD WORKER.

937
00:48:50,067 --> 00:48:54,066
HE WOULD BE IN HERE ALL HOURS
OF THE NIGHT, CREATING.

938
00:48:54,067 --> 00:48:58,632
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET
SOME INSPIRATION FROM THAT.

939
00:48:58,633 --> 00:49:01,232
INSPIRATION.

940
00:49:01,233 --> 00:49:03,732
I'M TRYING TO FIND
SOME OF THAT MYSELF.

941
00:49:03,733 --> 00:49:06,299
OH, ARE YOU WORKING
ON A PROJECT?

942
00:49:06,300 --> 00:49:07,367
YES.

943
00:49:11,333 --> 00:49:12,766
RIGHT.

944
00:49:12,767 --> 00:49:14,666
ABOUT THAT.

945
00:49:14,667 --> 00:49:18,467
IS YOUR OFFER TO READ
MY WORK ON THE TABLE?

946
00:49:20,967 --> 00:49:22,767
SURE.

947
00:49:24,567 --> 00:49:27,199
THANKS. GOOD NIGHT. GOOD NIGHT.

948
00:49:27,200 --> 00:49:28,599
THAT SOUNDS AWFUL.

949
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:29,866
YOU NEED ME TO COME DOWN THERE?

950
00:49:29,867 --> 00:49:31,332
I MEAN, I'LL SET THEM STRAIGHT.

951
00:49:31,333 --> 00:49:33,266
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE TO PUT UP
WITH ALL OF THAT THIS SOON.

952
00:49:33,267 --> 00:49:35,799
I HAVE TO GET THIS BOOK DONE.

953
00:49:35,800 --> 00:49:38,066
MAYBE I SHOULD JUST
STAY SOMEWHERE ELSE.

954
00:49:38,067 --> 00:49:39,432
NO.

955
00:49:39,433 --> 00:49:41,166
<i>YOU'RE BLOCKED BECAUSE
YOU HAVEN'T DONE THE WORK</i>

956
00:49:41,167 --> 00:49:42,799
<i>TO GET THE ANSWERS
THAT YOU NEED.</i>

957
00:49:42,800 --> 00:49:46,533
<i>KEEP AT IT, AND KEEP
YOUR RIGHT HOOK READY.</i>

958
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:51,966
EUGENE, I GOT TO TAKE THIS.

959
00:49:51,967 --> 00:49:54,799
<i>GET TO WORK.</i>

960
00:49:54,800 --> 00:49:56,399
HI, SABRINA.

961
00:49:56,400 --> 00:50:00,666
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO REACH YOU
FOREVER. I'M AT MY LIMIT, HALLE.

962
00:50:00,667 --> 00:50:03,399
SABRINA, YOU TOLD ME TO GET
YOU PAGES BY CHRISTMAS,

963
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,832
WHICH IS STILL A FEW
DAYS AWAY, RIGHT?

964
00:50:05,833 --> 00:50:07,999
<i>WELL, YES.</i>

965
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,066
THEN UNLESS YOU'RE
CALLING TO OFFER ME

966
00:50:10,067 --> 00:50:13,599
SOME WORDS OF ENCOURAGEMENT,
I'D RATHER GET BACK TO WORK.

967
00:50:13,600 --> 00:50:14,966
<i>SHE'S BACK!</i>

968
00:50:14,967 --> 00:50:16,767
THIS IS THE HALLE
I LOVE TO FIGHT FOR.

969
00:50:17,367 --> 00:50:21,900
YEAH.

970
00:50:27,767 --> 00:50:30,632
IS THAT A "DEAR JOAN" LETTER?

971
00:50:30,633 --> 00:50:33,499
NO, IT'S NOTHING.

972
00:50:33,500 --> 00:50:35,566
ALRIGHT, YOU TWO.

973
00:50:35,567 --> 00:50:38,732
IT'S ALMOST CHRISTMAS,
NOW MAKE UP.

974
00:50:38,733 --> 00:50:40,032
IF NOT FOR ME, DO IT FOR MEMAW.

975
00:50:40,033 --> 00:50:42,299
IF NOT FOR ME AND MEMAW,
DO IT FOR DREW, SANTA,

976
00:50:42,300 --> 00:50:44,466
WHOEVER YOU NEED IT TO BE.

977
00:50:44,467 --> 00:50:49,132
YOU FIRST.

978
00:50:49,133 --> 00:50:51,332
I'M SORRY, HALLE.

979
00:50:51,333 --> 00:50:54,233
THAT WAS A VERY IMMATURE
THING THAT I DID TO YOU.

980
00:50:56,900 --> 00:51:01,767
FOR MEMAW AND DREW, THERE
WILL BE NO PAYBACK TODAY.

981
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:06,766
Y'ALL CAN'T FEEL
THE CHRISTMAS SPIRIT?

982
00:51:06,767 --> 00:51:08,166
SURE,

983
00:51:08,167 --> 00:51:11,432
BUT I NEED TO GO PREPARE
FOR THE GREEN CARPET TOMORROW.

984
00:51:11,433 --> 00:51:13,067
SHE INVITED HER GIRLFRIEND.

985
00:51:14,967 --> 00:51:16,732
IF SHE'S GONNA BE IN
TOWN FOR THE EVENT,

986
00:51:16,733 --> 00:51:19,066
YOU SHOULD INVITE HER TO
SPEND TIME WITH YOUR FAMILY.

987
00:51:19,067 --> 00:51:21,632
NOW, SHE'S ONLY IN TOWN
TO SUPPORT THE ARTISTS

988
00:51:21,633 --> 00:51:24,166
BECAUSE THEY USED
TO TOUR TOGETHER.

989
00:51:24,167 --> 00:51:27,067
SHE LEAVES ON A RED-EYE
AFTER THE CHESS SLAM.

990
00:51:32,133 --> 00:51:35,266
IF SHE'S COMING ALL THE WAY
OUT HERE, YOU SHOULD INVITE HER.

991
00:51:35,267 --> 00:51:36,899
I GOT ON A PLANE NOT
KNOWING ANY OF YOU,

992
00:51:36,900 --> 00:51:39,499
AND I'VE NEVER BEEN MORE
NERVOUS TO MEET ANYONE,

993
00:51:39,500 --> 00:51:41,166
BUT IT FELT GOOD TO BE INVITED.

994
00:51:41,167 --> 00:51:42,599
INVITING HER WILL
MAKE HER FEEL LIKE

995
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:47,132
YOU'RE REALLY LETTING HER IN,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

996
00:51:47,133 --> 00:51:48,932
THAT IS WHAT I WANT.

997
00:51:48,933 --> 00:51:50,766
THEN LISTEN TO HALLE.

998
00:51:50,767 --> 00:51:52,332
AT LEAST INVITE HER
TO THE CHESS SLAM.

999
00:51:52,333 --> 00:51:54,466
YOU CAN LET HER DECIDE
IF IT'S TOO MUCH.

1000
00:51:54,467 --> 00:51:56,732
SHE MIGHT SURPRISE YOU.
IT'S CHRISTMAS.

1001
00:51:56,733 --> 00:52:00,399
THERE'S NO BETTER TIME TO
MAKE THIS REALLY GOOD CHOICE.

1002
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:01,699
MM-HMM.

1003
00:52:01,700 --> 00:52:05,067
IT'S HER.

1004
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:07,332
<i>HEY, BABY.</i>

1005
00:52:07,333 --> 00:52:09,499
<i>I ONLY GOT A SECOND.
I'M AT THE STUDIO,</i>

1006
00:52:09,500 --> 00:52:11,866
<i>AND THE DESIGNER
SENT THE DRESSES.</i>

1007
00:52:11,867 --> 00:52:13,632
<i>WHICH ONE AM I
WEARING TOMORROW NIGHT?</i>

1008
00:52:13,633 --> 00:52:14,766
JUST BRING THEM BOTH,

1009
00:52:14,767 --> 00:52:17,066
AND WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT
WHEN I SEE THEM.

1010
00:52:17,067 --> 00:52:19,766
<i>GOT IT. I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.</i>

1011
00:52:19,767 --> 00:52:20,932
WILL YOU COME WITH ME

1012
00:52:20,933 --> 00:52:22,266
TO MY LITTLE BROTHER'S
CHESS SLAM?

1013
00:52:22,267 --> 00:52:24,632
PLEASE. CHESS IS HIS LIFE.

1014
00:52:24,633 --> 00:52:26,099
BABE?

1015
00:52:26,100 --> 00:52:28,766
WILL YOU COME WITH ME TO
MY BROTHER'S CHESS SLAM?

1016
00:52:28,767 --> 00:52:32,699
IT'S HOURS BEFORE YOUR FLIGHT.
MY WHOLE FAMILY WILL BE THERE.

1017
00:52:32,700 --> 00:52:35,166
<i>WHICH BROTHER? THE LITTLE ONE?</i>

1018
00:52:35,167 --> 00:52:39,766
<i>OH, IF IT'S HIM, YES.
GLENN? NO WAY.</i>

1019
00:52:39,767 --> 00:52:42,499
YES, MY BABY BROTHER, DREW.

1020
00:52:42,500 --> 00:52:43,799
<i>WOW.</i>

1021
00:52:43,800 --> 00:52:46,799
<i>I FINALLY GET TO MEET
THE REST OF THE FAMILY?</i>

1022
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:50,466
<i>SHOOT ME THE DEETS,
I'LL BE THERE.</i>

1023
00:52:50,467 --> 00:52:52,432
<i>I GOT TO GO, BABE.</i>

1024
00:52:52,433 --> 00:52:54,933
OKAY. <i>BYE, GLENN.</i>

1025
00:52:58,133 --> 00:53:01,066
<i>BYE.</i>

1026
00:53:01,067 --> 00:53:03,699
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW EASY THAT WAS.

1027
00:53:03,700 --> 00:53:05,532
YOU WERE RIGHT, HALLE.

1028
00:53:05,533 --> 00:53:07,199
I HELPED TOO.

1029
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:08,699
WOULD YOU MIND DROPPING ME OFF

1030
00:53:08,700 --> 00:53:10,199
AT THE STORE
ON YOUR WAY TO WORK?

1031
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:12,566
ONLY IF YOU MEET US
SOMEWHERE AFTER.

1032
00:53:12,567 --> 00:53:14,333
OKAY, LET ME GET MY COAT.

1033
00:53:24,067 --> 00:53:26,599
YOU MADE A MIRACLE
HAPPEN TODAY, OLDEST SISTER.

1034
00:53:26,600 --> 00:53:28,432
TIFFANY AND PARIS
MAKE EACH OTHER HAPPY,

1035
00:53:28,433 --> 00:53:31,366
AND WE COULD ALL USE SOME
MORE OF THAT RIGHT NOW.

1036
00:53:31,367 --> 00:53:33,299
WELL, MAYBE THIS WAS
A GIRL THING.

1037
00:53:33,300 --> 00:53:36,299
SHE JUST NEEDED
SOME SISTERLY ADVICE.

1038
00:53:36,300 --> 00:53:37,932
GLENN, I THINK HALLE IS RIGHT,

1039
00:53:37,933 --> 00:53:39,799
AND WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

1040
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:43,066
"OLD" IS NO BETTER THAN "BIG."

1041
00:53:43,067 --> 00:53:45,066
I'M GLAD IT WORKED OUT.

1042
00:53:45,067 --> 00:53:47,532
I'M STARTING TO GAIN
SOME PERSPECTIVE

1043
00:53:47,533 --> 00:53:50,099
ON HOW THINGS RUN
IN THIS FAMILY.

1044
00:53:50,100 --> 00:53:52,766
OH, LIKE WHAT?

1045
00:53:52,767 --> 00:53:55,099
LIKE REALIZING THERE'S
A LEARNING CURVE

1046
00:53:55,100 --> 00:53:56,599
TO BEING A SISTER.

1047
00:53:56,600 --> 00:53:58,232
MAYBE IF WE HELP EACH OTHER,

1048
00:53:58,233 --> 00:54:01,699
THE REST WILL JUST
FALL INTO PLACE.

1049
00:54:01,700 --> 00:54:04,899
DO YOU KNOW WHY WE BROUGHT
YOU HERE TWICE NOW?

1050
00:54:04,900 --> 00:54:07,199
BECAUSE THE FOOD IS GOOD?

1051
00:54:07,200 --> 00:54:09,766
DADDY BROUGHT US HERE
FOR EVERY SPECIAL OCCASION.

1052
00:54:09,767 --> 00:54:13,266
THIS IS ONE OF HIS
FAVORITE PLACES.

1053
00:54:13,267 --> 00:54:15,199
IT'S ONE OF YOUR TRADITIONS?

1054
00:54:15,200 --> 00:54:16,699
IT'S A DAD TRADITION.

1055
00:54:16,700 --> 00:54:19,432
I GUESS YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THAT BEFORE BECAUSE...

1056
00:54:19,433 --> 00:54:22,432
WE WEREN'T READY.

1057
00:54:22,433 --> 00:54:23,866
I GET IT.

1058
00:54:23,867 --> 00:54:27,732
YOU KNOW, YOU HAVE
SOME OF HIS MANNERISMS.

1059
00:54:27,733 --> 00:54:31,399
BIG TIME. Y'ALL
SMILE JUST THE SAME.

1060
00:54:31,400 --> 00:54:33,432
SO JUST KNOW, WE KNOW
YOU'RE ONE OF US,

1061
00:54:33,433 --> 00:54:36,366
EVEN IF WE DON'T ALWAYS SAY
IT, BECAUSE IT'S AWKWARD.

1062
00:54:36,367 --> 00:54:37,566
YEAH.

1063
00:54:37,567 --> 00:54:39,066
THANK YOU.

1064
00:54:39,067 --> 00:54:41,899
THAT MEANS A LOT.

1065
00:54:41,900 --> 00:54:43,332
NOT TO BREAK
THE MOOD OR ANYTHING,

1066
00:54:43,333 --> 00:54:45,532
BUT MAY I ASK YOU SOME QUESTIONS
ABOUT A CONCEPT YOU INSPIRED?

1067
00:54:45,533 --> 00:54:48,566
I DID? WHAT WAS IT?

1068
00:54:48,567 --> 00:54:51,099
IT'S AN APP THAT CONNECTS PEOPLE
TO FAMILIES DURING THE HOLIDAYS

1069
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:54,099
OR WHENEVER PEOPLE ARE IN NEED
OF SOME EXTENDED FAMILY.

1070
00:54:54,100 --> 00:54:55,932
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

1071
00:54:55,933 --> 00:54:58,166
FROM COLLEGE KIDS THAT CAN'T
GET HOME FOR THE HOLIDAYS

1072
00:54:58,167 --> 00:55:00,432
TO SENIORS WHO DON'T
HAVE FAMILIES...

1073
00:55:00,433 --> 00:55:02,632
THERE'S A MARKET FOR THAT.

1074
00:55:02,633 --> 00:55:07,233
LOOK AT YOU GUYS BUILDING
A BUSINESS IN DADDY'S HOTEL.

1075
00:55:09,467 --> 00:55:10,866
ALL I KNOW IS, HOWEVER IT GOES,

1076
00:55:10,867 --> 00:55:12,966
I WANT TO HANDLE ALL THE PRESS

1077
00:55:12,967 --> 00:55:15,332
DEAL. OKAY.

1078
00:55:15,333 --> 00:55:17,067
CHEERS. CHEERS.

1079
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:23,699
THEY'RE GOING TO LOVE YOU.

1080
00:55:23,700 --> 00:55:26,166
WELCOME. YOU ALMOST GOT LEFT.

1081
00:55:26,167 --> 00:55:29,199
WELL, IT'S GOOD TO SEE
YOU, TOO, GLENN.

1082
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:33,132
MEMAW, HALLE, DEVIN,
THIS IS PARIS.

1083
00:55:33,133 --> 00:55:34,599
PARIS, THIS IS MY FAMILY.

1084
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:36,466
WELCOME, PARIS.

1085
00:55:36,467 --> 00:55:39,832
WE HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT YOU
FROM TIFFANY AND GLENN.

1086
00:55:39,833 --> 00:55:43,599
OH, THANK YOU.
THE PLEASURE IS MINE.

1087
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:47,466
AND GLENN, YOU ARE GETTING
FOUR BACKSTAGE PASSES

1088
00:55:47,467 --> 00:55:49,932
TO MY NEW YEAR'S SHOW IN L.A.

1089
00:55:49,933 --> 00:55:54,432
WE'LL PAUSE OUR TEASING
FOR ONE NIGHT.

1090
00:55:54,433 --> 00:55:55,699
LOVE HAVING SISTERS.

1091
00:55:55,700 --> 00:55:58,967
IF YOU'RE DONE DANCING,
WE CAN GET TO THE SLAM.

1092
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:05,866
TIFF TOLD ME WHAT
YOU SAID TO HER.

1093
00:56:05,867 --> 00:56:07,232
I DIDN'T DO MUCH.

1094
00:56:07,233 --> 00:56:10,366
SHE JUST NEEDED A LITTLE PUSH
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION.

1095
00:56:10,367 --> 00:56:12,633
WELL, THANK YOU FOR THAT PUSH.

1096
00:56:20,600 --> 00:56:22,766
CHECK IT OUT! I WON!

1097
00:56:22,767 --> 00:56:25,799
WOW. THIS IS AMAZING.

1098
00:56:25,800 --> 00:56:28,966
YEAH, IT IS! CAN'T
BELIEVE I WON.

1099
00:56:28,967 --> 00:56:32,766
DID YOU EVER GET A CHANCE TO
REVIEW THAT EDIT I LEFT FOR YOU?

1100
00:56:32,767 --> 00:56:36,299
WHAT ARE YOU EDITING,
SISTER DEAR?

1101
00:56:36,300 --> 00:56:40,232
GREAT. SORRY.

1102
00:56:40,233 --> 00:56:43,966
HALLE IS REVIEWING
SOMETHING I'M WRITING.

1103
00:56:43,967 --> 00:56:45,432
YOU'RE A WRITER, MAMA?

1104
00:56:45,433 --> 00:56:48,599
SHE IS, AND IT'S EXCELLENT.

1105
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:51,299
WOW. THAT'S AWESOME, JOAN.

1106
00:56:51,300 --> 00:56:53,366
IT'S ONLY MY FIRST CHAPTER.

1107
00:56:53,367 --> 00:56:56,632
SOMETIMES THAT'S ALL IT TAKES.

1108
00:56:56,633 --> 00:57:00,400
AND YOU KNOW THIS FROM YOUR
WEALTH OF EXPERIENCE PROOFING?

1109
00:57:07,200 --> 00:57:08,932
JOAN, YOU'RE RIGHT.

1110
00:57:08,933 --> 00:57:10,967
I AM KEEPING SOMETHING FROM YOU.

1111
00:57:14,967 --> 00:57:18,099
I WRITE BOOKS.

1112
00:57:18,100 --> 00:57:22,732
PUBLISHED BOOKS.
I'M H.D. MADISON.

1113
00:57:22,733 --> 00:57:26,399
<i>THE</i> H.D. MADISON?

1114
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:31,266
SOLD LIKE A JILLION COPIES THAT
ARE PROBABLY GONNA BE MOVIES?

1115
00:57:31,267 --> 00:57:34,932
WHY NOT JUST TELL US
YOU'RE A FAMOUS AUTHOR?

1116
00:57:34,933 --> 00:57:38,599
I WANTED YOU TO GET TO KNOW
HALLE DOWNING FIRST.

1117
00:57:38,600 --> 00:57:41,832
AND JOAN, YOUR WORK INSPIRED ME.

1118
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:43,766
<i>I'VE</i> EVEN BEEN TRYING
TO WRITE MY NEXT BOOK,

1119
00:57:43,767 --> 00:57:47,066
AND I NEED TO BE MORE CONFIDENT.

1120
00:57:47,067 --> 00:57:50,066
SO YOU'RE WRITING ABOUT US?

1121
00:57:50,067 --> 00:57:53,232
NOT ABOUT YOU, BUT INSPIRED BY.

1122
00:57:53,233 --> 00:57:57,299
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU, HALLE.

1123
00:57:57,300 --> 00:57:58,966
HERE, CAN I HAVE YOUR AUTOGRAPH?

1124
00:57:58,967 --> 00:58:01,266
SURE. YES.

1125
00:58:01,267 --> 00:58:02,633
SURE.

1126
00:58:06,067 --> 00:58:07,467
WHAT DO YOU WANT IT TO SAY?

1127
00:58:11,067 --> 00:58:12,966
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

1128
00:58:12,967 --> 00:58:15,132
I WAS RIGHT ABOUT HER.

1129
00:58:15,133 --> 00:58:17,066
SHE'S BEEN LYING
TO US ALL ALONG,

1130
00:58:17,067 --> 00:58:19,799
AND NOW SHE'S SECRETLY
A FAMOUS AUTHOR

1131
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:22,232
WORTHY OF OUR PRAISE?

1132
00:58:22,233 --> 00:58:24,432
TONIGHT IS ABOUT DREW.

1133
00:58:24,433 --> 00:58:27,666
LET'S HAVE OUR CELEBRATION
AS WE PLANNED.

1134
00:58:27,667 --> 00:58:30,800
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY,
AND I'M TIRED.

1135
00:58:32,233 --> 00:58:35,066
DREW, BABY, COME TELL ME
GOOD NIGHT BEFORE YOU GO TO BED.

1136
00:58:35,067 --> 00:58:36,867
WELL, IMAGINE IF YOU
MADE A BOOK ABOUT ME.

1137
00:58:39,200 --> 00:58:40,767
HE DIDN'T EVEN HEAR ME.

1138
00:58:42,767 --> 00:58:45,899
YOU ALL ARE MAKING IT SO EASY
FOR HER TO BECOME A MOORE

1139
00:58:45,900 --> 00:58:49,066
IN A WAY YOU DIDN'T FOR ME.

1140
00:58:49,067 --> 00:58:51,133
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE SAYING THIS.

1141
00:59:01,700 --> 00:59:04,899
THANK YOU ALL
FOR BEING HERE TODAY.

1142
00:59:04,900 --> 00:59:07,466
BEFORE EACH SEAT,
THERE IS A SEALED ENVELOPE

1143
00:59:07,467 --> 00:59:11,466
THAT CONTAINS THE SPECIFIC
DETAILS OF YOUR DISTRIBUTION.

1144
00:59:11,467 --> 00:59:15,166
BUT BEFORE WE GO OVER THAT,
WE HAVE A VIDEO TO PLAY,

1145
00:59:15,167 --> 00:59:18,400
SO MR. MOORE CAN EXPLAIN
SOME THINGS HIMSELF.

1146
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:23,866
<i>HELLO, FAMILY.</i>

1147
00:59:23,867 --> 00:59:26,399
<i>DON'T WORRY, YOU'LL BE SMILING
BY THE END OF THIS.</i>

1148
00:59:26,400 --> 00:59:29,099
<i>I DON'T WANT ANY CONFUSION
WHEN IT COMES TO MY AFFAIRS,</i>

1149
00:59:29,100 --> 00:59:30,599
<i>SO MY ATTORNEY HAS
BEEN INSTRUCTED</i>

1150
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:32,866
<i>TO FOLLOW MY WISHES
TO THE LETTER...</i>

1151
00:59:32,867 --> 00:59:36,632
<i>AND FOR THAT, CANDACE,
I THANK YOU.</i>

1152
00:59:36,633 --> 00:59:40,066
<i>TO DREW, TIFFANY, AND
GLENN... LOVE YOU ALL.</i>

1153
00:59:40,067 --> 00:59:43,499
<i>GO BE SUCCESSFUL,
TAKE CARE OF EACH OTHER,</i>

1154
00:59:43,500 --> 00:59:45,432
<i>AND KEEP DOING
ALL OUR FUN STUFF.</i>

1155
00:59:45,433 --> 00:59:47,867
<i>AND BOYS, YES, TIFFANY
IS THE BOSS OF YOU GUYS.</i>

1156
00:59:50,067 --> 00:59:56,166
<i>BUT THEN AGAIN, THERE IS
STRENGTH IN NUMBERS, RIGHT?</i>

1157
00:59:56,167 --> 00:59:57,799
DADDY... YOU HEARD THE MAN.

1158
00:59:57,800 --> 01:00:01,799
<i>DEVIN, MY MAN.
YOU MADE ME PROUD.</i>

1159
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:04,632
<i>GET THAT RESTAURANT STARTED.</i>

1160
01:00:04,633 --> 01:00:10,366
<i>YOU DON'T HAVE TO NAME IT
"HOWARD'S" UNLESS YOU WANT TO</i>...

1161
01:00:10,367 --> 01:00:12,900
<i>BUT, YOU KNOW, NO PRESSURE.</i>

1162
01:00:16,067 --> 01:00:19,466
<i>MAMA, YOU GAVE ME EVERYTHING.</i>

1163
01:00:19,467 --> 01:00:22,999
<i>ALL MY SUCCESS IS YOURS, TOO.</i>

1164
01:00:23,000 --> 01:00:25,266
<i>I KNOW YOU THINK
I SPOILED EVERYONE,</i>

1165
01:00:25,267 --> 01:00:29,832
<i>BUT WHERE DO YOU
THINK I LEARNED IT?</i>

1166
01:00:29,833 --> 01:00:34,066
<i>JOAN, MY BELOVED WIFE.</i>

1167
01:00:34,067 --> 01:00:38,332
<i>I KNOW I AM AMAZING
IN EVERY WAY POSSIBLE...</i>

1168
01:00:38,333 --> 01:00:40,232
<i>HANDSOME, THOUGHTFUL,</i>

1169
01:00:40,233 --> 01:00:42,666
<i>AND I GAVE THE BEST
ANNIVERSARY GIFTS,</i>

1170
01:00:42,667 --> 01:00:47,999
<i>AND EVEN WHEN I FORGOT, YOU
TOOK IT OUT ON MY CREDIT CARDS.</i>

1171
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:50,699
<i>I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW,</i>

1172
01:00:50,700 --> 01:00:55,699
<i>BEING YOUR HUSBAND
MADE ME A VERY LUCKY MAN.</i>

1173
01:00:55,700 --> 01:00:57,267
<i>I LOVE YOU, SWEETHEART.</i>

1174
01:01:02,333 --> 01:01:06,466
<i>AND TO HALLE, IF YOU'RE THERE</i>...

1175
01:01:06,467 --> 01:01:09,866
<i>NOT A DAY PASSED THAT
I DIDN'T THINK ABOUT YOU.</i>

1176
01:01:09,867 --> 01:01:14,399
<i>I PRAY THAT THE FAMILY CAN DO
FOR YOU NOW WHAT I COULDN'T,</i>

1177
01:01:14,400 --> 01:01:20,099
<i>AND KNOW THIS... I'M A FAN.</i>

1178
01:01:20,100 --> 01:01:21,732
<i>SO CHEER UP, FAMILY,</i>

1179
